CONGRATS ARGENTINA 2022 WORLD CUP CHAMPIONS! 🇦🇷🏆

MISSION ACCOMPLISHED and DESTINY fulfilled for THE BEST IN THE WORLD @leomessi in The Beautiful Game!

LOOK UP GOAT in the Dictionary or GOOGLE IT and you will find MESSI! The debate is over! He is the KING of SOCCER and has done it all! I still think PELE is the greatest ever winning 3 WORLD CUPS but LEO deserves to be in the conversation and a spot with the elite and soccer royalty! 

LIONEL MESSI is a WORLD CUP CHAMPION for the first time and 3rd time for ARGENTINA who previously won in 1978 and 1986! 

We experienced one of the most exciting Finals in WORLD CUP History well next to the AZZURRI winning in 1982 and 2006! 😁🇮🇹

Argentina took a 2 NIL lead in on goals from MESSI and DI MARIA! MBAPPE had an extraordinary game in the losing effort and scored 2 late goals in regulation time within 97 seconds and sent the match into Extra Time! MESSI scored his 2nd and Mbappe his 3rd to make it 3-3 in overtime and both scored in the shootout.

ARGENTINA WON 4-2 on Penalty Kicks and knocked off the 2018 Champions FRANCE! 

This is an incredible story considering Argentina was shocked and stunned suffering  an opening match loss to Saudi Arabia. MESSI said after the game that the dressing room was dead but they ressurected and overcame the embarrassment and on December 18, 2022 crowned Champions of The World! 💙

FUN FACT: My NONNA was born in Argentina and my Dad's Brother lived there and we still have family in Santa Fe! Without ITALY the reigning EUROPEAN CHAMPIONS in the tournament and Canada el8minated the first round I was cheering for ARG to win it all from the start entering WORLD CUP 2022 ranked 3rd behind Brazil and Belgium.

THANK YOU FRANCO!  REST IN PEACE MR PITTSBURGH! 💛🙏

This one hurts me and my fellow Steelers Nation big time. 💔

FRANCO HARRIS an Italian African American was the reason I became a STEELERS fan! 2 of my childhood heroes have sadly passed away in 2022 including GUY LAFLEUR @canadiensmtl on April 22 and FRANCO on December 20, 2022 ❤️

FRANCO caught the World Famous IMMACULATE RECEPTION in his rookie season on DECEMBER 23, 1972 vs Okland Raiers in a dramatic 13-7 victory at Three Rivers Stadium. Its been called the greatest, most iconic and controversial catches in NFL History! 

FRANCO HARRIS had an amazing career and went on to WIN 4 SUPER BOWLS and scored a TD in all appearances. He was a SUPER BOWL MVP, 9 Appearances in the Pro Bowl, Man of The Year and won many other awards, accoladesand accomplishments.

HARRIS rushed for 12,120 Yards and scored 91 rushing Touchdowns and caught 307 passes for 2287 yards and 9 receiving TDs mostly with @steelers and played his final season with @seahawks.

FRANCO HARRIS was inducted into the NFL HALL of FAME in 1990, New Jersey HALL of FAME in 2011 and the STEELERS HALL of HONOR in 2017.

If you're ever at the Pittsburgh International Airport make sure you pose and take a selfie with FRANCO's Iconic Life Size Statue right next to George Washington.

No Steelers player has ever worn #32 since his departure but finally his Jersey will be officially retired this Saturday during the @raiders game in Pittsburgh. FRANCO was scheduled to attend the ceremony but sadly  passed away at the age of 72. Mean Joe Green #75 and Ernie Stautner #70 are the only other jerseys retired by The Black & Gold!

REST IN PARADISE PELE 🙏

Sad to hear the legendary PELE passed away at the age of 82. 💔

We often engage in debates, discussions and arguments of who the GOAT is! MESSI and RONALDO are both in that conversation but was there ever a greater player, star, trailblazer and ambassador of Soccer/Football than PELE who was a 3X WORLD CUP CHAMPION with BRAZIL in 1958, 1962 and 1970🏆🏆🏆

Sad to.hear the legendary Hazel McCallion, former longtime mayor of Mississauga for 36 years passed away at the age of 101 just shy of her 102nd birthday on February 14. 💔

Sending our thoughts and prayers and condolences to her family and loved ones. 🙏

Hazel lived an incredible life! A Life With Putpose! ❤️

I was honored to co-host her Retirement Party...... wait her Appreciation Party as she made it clear she would never retire! 

I chatted with Hazel at many events over the years and loved her spirit, energy and passion. She was still a fire cracker at 101! The last time I saw her was in June 2022 and looked great talking to fans and posing for pix. She was loved and respected by all!

Hazel told @rominajmonaco and I many times that the key to life is "keep moving" "keep working" and "don't stop" She lived by those words! She retired as Major in 2014 but continued to work and make a difference in her city and country and sat on several boards.

Ontario Premier @fordnationdougford said McCallion died peacefully at her home this morning in Mississauga. Ford said his dear friend and mentor was "the true definition of a public servant She led the transformation of Mississauga into one of Canada’s largest cities. Mississauga and Ontario are better places because of the amazing life of Hazel McCallion. Rest easy, my friend."

The Mayor of Mississauga @bonniecrombie praised her mentor and said "she built this city" and called Hazel a "fierce and passionate leader who touched the lives of so many."

Hurricane Hazel was a true leader and inspiration and often referred to as "Canada's Mayor" and when asked how she wanted to be remembered she said as "The People's Mayor"

Hazel McCallion is gone but will never be forgotten. She set the standard and made a major impact and contribution and leaves behind a lasting legacy. Thank You for your service Hazel.

Early Thursday Morning our Z1035 JEEP was STOLEN in the Yonge and 401 area Toronto.

@hammeronair and I first publicly reported the theft on Z1035 and Hammer spoke with @kerry_schmidt of the OPP on air Friday.

THANKS to the power of RADIO, RDS in Cars, Social Media and TIPS from our amazing Z1035 Listeners our JEEP was FOUND in Oshawa today secured by OPP and Durham Police. 🙏

Over 10,000 vehicles have been stolen in Toronto in 2023 up 45% from last year. 

We are fortunate to get our JEEP back. ❤️ 

We report and hear about thefts daily but never think it will happen to us. Sadly many people never get their cars back. 

When a car is stolen it can be be shipped out of thre country and resold, used in other crimes, chopped up to resell the parts or somebody looking for a thrill going on a Joyride! 

Ottawa reported an uptick in thefts of Jeep Wranglers/Gladiators followed by Toyota Highlanders, Honda CRVs and Dodge Ram Trucks.

88,000 cars were stolen in Canada in 2022 with Honda CRV at the Top of The Stolen List followed by Lexus RS, Ford F-150, Honda Civic, Toyota Highlander, RAM 1500 and Chev/GMC

Do not leave any valuables in your vehicles no matter where you park.

There are things we can do to deter thefts including locking doors, parking in garage if possible, use a steering wheel lock, Lock your Ports and use Digital Tracking and Immobilizers but even doing all these things doesn't guarantee your vehicle won't be stolen. I know people who have had 2 even 3 of their SUVs stolen. 

Let's hope Car Manufactuers, Authorities and Governments come up with new effective and affordable methods to stop the rise in thefts.

🇮🇹 The Majestic Alps 👑  This has to be one of the most glorious and #breathtaking places on planet  #Earth .  Born in the Italian #Alps, I've been coming here my entire life and feel very fortunate to know my past and heritage.🙏 #Italians from this area descend from the first #Celtic inhabitants and subsequent Roman and Barbarian invaders.  This culture is not Italian...or Austrian... or French .. or Swiss. It's uniquely #Alpine . 
Tony, whose background is Calabrian, is now an honourary member of this tribe .. he's even mastered driving these crazy mountain roads! Bravo!! 😆👍🇮🇹

Sad to hear the legendary SUZANNE SOMERS who starred in the iconic ‘THREE'S COMPANY'’ as CHRISSY SNOW and ‘She’s the Sheriff' and Step By Step aswell as an Author, Business Woman and Fitness, Health and Wellness Advocate and Spokesperson passed away at 76 just a day before her 77th Birthday on Monday.💔

Somers appeared as the "Blonde in the white Thunderbird" in American Graffiti and guest appearances on The Rockford Files, The Six Million Dollar Man, The Love Boat and One Day at a Time.

Suzanne married TV Host Alan Hamel in 1977 and was previously married to Bruce Somers 1965-68.

Somers told PEOPLE that she was planning on eating Short Rib Tacos and a "copious amounts of cake" on her birthday despite her recent health setbacks. She announced in July 2023 that her cancer had returned. 

She was planning to be with her “nearest and dearest” on her special day, including her "beloved husband Alan [Hamel], our three children, Leslie, Stephen, and Bruce, [his wife] Caroline, plus our six wonderful grandchildren.”

Her family will now do a celebration of life. ❤️

Suzanne Somers’ longtime publicist R. Couri Hay shared a statement on behalf of the family .

"Suzanne Somers passed away peacefully at home in the early morning hours of Oct. 15th. She survived an aggressive form of breast cancer for over 23 years. Suzanne was surrounded by her loving husband Alan, her son Bruce, and her immediate family. Her family was gathered to celebrate her 77th birthday on October 16th. Instead, they will celebrate her extraordinary life, and want to thank her millions of fans and followers who loved her dearly."

Suzanne leaves behind an incredible legacy. She was an inspirational woman that never gave up and battled for decades. Somers did what she believed was best for her life and body. 💜

❤️ ANOTHER LESSON LEARNED 🙏When I graduated high school I received one of the highest recognitions at my commencement ceremony. It was the Award of Merit given to a student who went above and beyond, exhibiting exceptional school spirit. To say I was shocked is a total understatement LOL. 😆 'Me? Why ME?' I was so honoured but lost that spirit because of all the exciting and fun events that sidetrack us in our youth. Fortunately, I found myself once again at age forty. Over the last decade I committed myself to community and being of service to something greater than myself. Why? Simply because of how amazing it made me feel, especially to see how happy people were when they received that special support! Wow...what a high! 👏

Then, a while back, I was hurt by a friend to the point where I wanted to walk away from it all. Why bother when you discover there are those you trust who will resort to anything just to knock you off your high? The pain was great. 🥺 My depression lasted over a year and I had trouble sleeping, writing, attending events and even turned down organizations in need of support. Tony became my strength - 'Don't look around you. Put your blinders on. Keep going,' he'd say. Seeing my state, he kept at it. 'The work you did with Dr. Mike helped so many women...keep doing it. Vaughan Together was vital during Covid. It's not right to stop important work because of ONE incident.' Tony fueled me and Vaughan Together went on to support the crippling food insecurity crisis...and slowly I began feeling better. 🙏 

However, what truly healed me were videos sent by a friend who lost his wife to cancer. These were first-hand accounts of NDEs (near death experiences) - a phenomena experienced by close to 20% of Americans in critically-ill situations. After hearing their stories, I knew that the overwhelming evidence including the uncanny similarities between cases couldn't be ignored. Although my family had several inexplicable, bizarre experiences since my mother's death and I was already a believer, it was these stories that helped me resolve the pain I felt. ❤️ ANOTHER LESSON LEARNED 🙏 (continued from previous post). I've learned that life is indeed a classroom. We come here to experience resistance, overcome obstacles and grow. Each human is interconnected and when you hurt someone you only damage yourself.  Be aware of every action you take and every word you say because IT WILL come back to you like a boomerang - good and bad. 👍

The energy you emit ripples, making endless waves affecting the world around you. There's no competition and there's enough for all. Lighten up, laugh often, be brave, create and know that what is not visible to the human eye always has your back. You are always being supported - no matter how tough a situation is!💪 
Earth is our stage where we play our various parts in order to learn and grow (thanks Shakespeare!). And whatever lessons were left unlearned you WILL come back to experience them all over again. And the big one (quoting The Beatles 😆), 'all you need is love'.  If you don't know how to resolve something just surrender.  The answer will come sooner or later. So, here I am finding my footing again and doing what we're all destined to do - live the best and most positive version of ourselves. What you give to the world, you get back.❤️🙏
